SIMPLE: justness
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Justness
<hw>Just"ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The quality of being just;
conformity to truth, propriety, accuracy, exactness, and the like;
justice; reasonableness; fairness; equity; <as>as, <ex>justness</ex> of
proportions; the <ex>justness</ex> of a description or representation;
the <ex>justness</ex> of a cause.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In value the satisfaction I had in seeing it represented with all
the <qex>justness</qex> and gracefulness of action.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ <xex>Justness</xex> is properly applied to things, and
<xex>justice</xex> to persons; but the distinction is not always
observed.</note></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Accuracy; exactness; correctness; propriety;
fitness; reasonableness; equity; uprightness; justice.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Jut</ent>⟦br⟧
